definition: to exceed/to overtake/to surpass/to transcend/to pass/to cross/ultra-/super-
to cross/to go over/to pass (time)/to celebrate (a holiday)/to live/to get along/excessively/too-
to exceed/to go beyond/to overstep the limit

sentences.english: This will launch XCOR into the emerging space tourism market, estimated at over a half-billion dollars.
sentences.chinese: 公司将投资超过五亿美金，来拓展空间旅游市场。

sentences.english: The major technique norms have over taken those of importations.
sentences.chinese: 主要技术指标超过原进口产品。

sentences.english: State-of-the-art systems report producing biogas that is more than 95% pure methane.
sentences.chinese: 最新系统报告产生的沼气中甲烷的含量超过95%。

sentences.english: He does exceedingly abundantly above and beyond what we could ever ask, imagine or think!
sentences.chinese: 神能充充足足的成就一切，超过我们所求所想的。

sentences.english: Now, more than 60 percent of kindergarteners attend for a full day.
sentences.chinese: 而现在，超过百分之六十的幼儿参加了全托。

sentences.english: They looked at long-term sick leave (of over 90 days) and hospital admission rates.
sentences.chinese: 他们关注的重点是超过90天的长时间病假和住院率。

sentences.english: We had better take less than 65 grammes fat every day.
sentences.chinese: 每天摄入的脂肪量最好不要超过65克。

sentences.english: First of all, it will only be a minute or two at a time, maybe once or twice a lecture.
sentences.chinese: 首先，每次只有一两分钟，一堂课最多不超过两次。

sentences.english: Over 22 million doses of squalene-containing flu vaccine have been administered.
sentences.chinese: 已接种的含角鲨烯流感疫苗数量超过2200万剂。

sentences.english: If rent longer than 24 month, the rent & deposit is on request.
sentences.chinese: 如果租期希望超过2年，租金和押金另议。

sentences.english: But the snag was that the Manchus were outnumbered by Han troops in Beijing.
sentences.chinese: 但那时，北京的汉族军人数量已经超过了满族军人。

sentences.english: Diatoms are also quite numerous, with the estimated number of species exceeding one million.
sentences.chinese: 硅藻种类也相当多，估计超过1百万种。

sentences.english: Sometimes, there are over 1000 Africans attending mass.
sentences.chinese: 有时侯，会有超过1000名非洲人参加弥撒。

sentences.english: Moses therefore took the money of them that were above, and whom they had redeemed from the Levites.
sentences.chinese: 梅瑟就为那超过肋未人数而应赎回的人，征收了赎金。

sentences.english: "And the majority were having premarital sex, over 50 percent, " says Rosenbaum.
sentences.chinese: 他们中的大多数，超过50%有过婚前性行为。
